text_blocks.snippet: Michael Jackson was an American entertainer whose legendary career spanned over four decades.

list.snippet: Age: He passed away at the age of 50.
Current Residence Location: He does not have a current residence; he died on June 25, 2009, in Los Angeles, California. He is buried at Forest Lawn Memorial Park in Glendale, California.
Occupations: His career included roles as a singer, songwriter, dancer, music producer, choreographer, actor, businessman, and philanthropist.

text_blocks.snippet: Michael Jackson was a "virtuoso" who often composed entire songs in his head without being able to read or write traditional music notation.

list.snippet: Vocals (Mastery): He possessed a four-octave vocal range (High Tenor) and was highly proficient in complex vocal techniques, including beatboxing, layering, and his signature "vocal percussion".
Dance (Mastery): Widely regarded as one of the greatest dancers in history, he popularized iconic moves like the moonwalk and the anti-gravity lean.
Songwriting/Composing (High Proficiency): He wrote many of his greatest hits, such as "Billie Jean" and "Beat It," by vocalizing every instrument's part into a recorder for producers to transcribe.

Instruments (Limited Proficiency): While he is credited with playing keyboards, guitar, and drums on some albums (e.g., HIStory), he was not considered a proficient instrumentalist and generally relied on professional musicians for the final recordings.
Music Production/Arranging (High Proficiency): He was a technical "musical architect" who was deeply involved in the fine details of sound engineering and studio production.
